Set free-space thresholds for Main. Thresholds are **remaining free space** (how much free is left), in units like `8T` or `500G`.

| Free space vs thresholds | Main free bar |
|--------------------------|---------------|
| Still **above** all thresholds | Normal Unraid look — or optional **green outline** if Outline style + “green when OK” |
| At or below **Warning** | **Yellow** (warning) |
| At or below **Critical** | **Red** (critical) |

**None** (or a blank custom field) turns that level off.

**Usual order:** Warning = larger free amount (earlier heads-up), Critical = **smaller** free amount (more severe).  
If both are set, the plugin always uses **severity by free-space amount**: the **lower** free amount is treated as critical (red), the **higher** as warning (yellow)—even if you assign the numbers the other way around. A notice appears below if Critical is set higher than Warning.

Highlight style is for the **array** (primary focus of this plugin). **Solid** (default) recolors the free fill yellow/red. **Outline** keeps Unraid’s fill and draws a border (yellow/red, optional pulse; optional green when still OK). Pool options are under Advanced (WIP).

